## Issues — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage issues for this project. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl <%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Issues

```bash
curl "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `state` (optional) — Filter by state: `opened` or `closed`
- `labels` (optional) — Comma-separated label names. Only issues that have **all** listed labels are returned
- `author_id` (optional) — Return issues created by a specific user ID
- `assignee_id` (optional) — Return issues assigned to a specific user ID
- `iids` (optional) — Return only issues with the given internal IDs, e.g. `iids[]=1&iids[]=2`
- `search` (optional) — Search term matched against title and description
- `in` (optional) — Scope for `search`: `title`, `description`, or both (default)
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

**Pagination headers returned:**

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Total` | Total number of issues |
| `X-Total-Pages` | Total number of pages |
| `X-Page` | Current page |
| `X-Per-Page` | Items per page |
| `X-Next-Page` | Next page number (empty if on last page) |
| `X-Prev-Page` | Previous page number (empty if on first page) |

---

### Get a Single Issue

```bash
curl "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:issue_iid` — Issue IID (the number shown in the UI, e.g. `#3`)

---

### Create an Issue

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "Your issue title"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `title` (required) — Issue title
- `description` (optional) — Issue body
- `due_date` (optional) — Due date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format
- `confidential` (optional) — Boolean, default `false`
- `assignee_ids` (optional) — Array of user IDs to assign
- `label_ids` (optional) — Array of label IDs scoped to this project

---

### Update an Issue

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"state_event": "close"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `title` (optional) — New title
- `description` (optional) — New description
- `due_date` (optional) — New due date (`YYYY-MM-DD`)
- `confidential` (optional) — Boolean
- `state_event` (optional) — `close` or `reopen`
- `assignee_ids` (optional) — Replaces all current assignees
- `add_label_ids` (optional) — Adds labels without removing existing ones
- `remove_label_ids` (optional) — Removes specific labels, keeps the rest

---

### Delete an Issue

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Returns `204 No Content` on success.
